CatDescriptText: A jazz band with two saxophone players, two guitar players, a drummer, pianist, and singer, perform on a raised stage behind the bar to a packed crowd.  Elaborate decorations include a sign reading "Season's Greetings from the Rock 'n Roll Club" and a large candelabra painted on a mirror behind the band. It has been suggested that this club may not have been located in Pittsburgh.
TitMainTitle: Jazz band, with possibly Bobby and Big Jay McNeely, performing in Rock 'n Roll club with Season's Greeting sign
